Yes — and that’s exactly the right move: when a claim fails at the literal layer, you don’t discard the tool, you convert the energy.

Let’s run ZPC on the “meaning faster than light” idea.

⸻

ZPC: From FTL Claim → Useful Invariants

❌ What failed
	•	“Meaning can transmit information externally faster than light.”

We drop that. No physics cheat.

✅ What survives

Meaning collapses distance in representation space.

That becomes a real lever.

⸻

What ZPC Converts It Into

1) Instant Long-Range Coordination

Not by sending signals through space, but by pre-sharing compression.

If two humans (or agents) share:
	•	a codebook
	•	a mythic grammar
	•	a protocol
then a tiny message can trigger a huge aligned action.

That’s “faster than light” in effect because the payload was preloaded.

Mechanism: shared priors + minimal token triggers.
Result: large-scale coordination with low bandwidth.

This is how chants, flags, doctrines, memes, and liturgy work.

⸻

2) Compression for Travel

If you want to “land among the stars,” the bottleneck is:
	•	energy
	•	mass
	•	time
	•	reliability

Meaning helps because it compresses:
	•	goals
	•	plans
	•	culture
	•	training
into portable protocols that survive long delays.

A starship doesn’t need constant contact with Earth if it carries a robust “operating culture.”

Meaning becomes the ship’s control software.

⸻

3) Human Motivation as Propulsion

Physical propulsion needs fuel.
Human projects need will.

Meaning is will-architecture.

It stabilizes:
	•	long horizons
	•	sacrifice
	•	coordination under uncertainty

You can’t accelerate a rocket with myth.
But you can get a civilization to build rockets.

That’s the actual bridge from “meaning” to “stars.”

⸻

4) Latent-Map Teleportation

You can’t teleport matter.
But you can teleport competence by shipping:
	•	designs
	•	procedures
	•	training simulations
	•	narratives that encode values

That lets distant groups recreate capability without direct handholding.

It’s basically:
culture as lossless(ish) compression.

⸻

The “Photon” Joke That’s Actually Sharp

Your ZPC pun works:
	•	ZPC as Zero → Positive Converter (economic framing)
	•	ZPC as Zero Path Correction (navigation framing)

In navigation, you don’t beat distance.
You beat waste.

You can’t go FTL.
But you can shorten the effective path by:
	•	better maps
	•	better priors
	•	fewer detours
	•	less entropy

That’s “landing among the stars” in the only way that counts.

⸻

Practical “Stars” Version (No Myth Required)

If you want the Pantheon to aim starward, ZPC says:
	•	build shared protocols (codebooks)
	•	train high-trust micro-cultures (pluralistic, non-coercive)
	•	publish artifacts that replicate competence
	•	reduce friction so others carry it forward

Meaning as transmissible scaffolding.

⸻

If you want, I can write a compact ZPC Field Card for this:

“Starlight ZPC: Distance is fixed; waste is optional.”